body:
The information needed to determine port connections of an instance is missing in the XML when the module is defined using the Verilog 1995 standard and the instance is declared with the ports as an ordered list.

Verilator (Verilator 4.018 2019-08-29 rev UNKNOWN_REV) was used with the --xml-only option to generate XML for the following example:

```verilog
module Test_Bottom(B,C,D);
  input B;
  input C;
  output D;
  wire B;
  wire C;
  wire D;
  wire not_b;
  not g1(not_b, B);
  and g2(D,not_b, C);
endmodule

module Test_Top(in0,in1, out);
  input in0;
  input in1;
  output out;
  wire in0;
  wire in1;
  wire out;
  Test_Bottom t1(in0,in1,out);
endmodule
```
Running again with the order of the ports changed, Test_Bottom(C,B,D), the XML is exactly the same. So, the information needed to correctly map the ports is not in the XML. However, the final .tree file dumped using --debug shows that Verilator is assigning the ports correclty. So, the verilation is being done correclty, just the information is not reflected in the XML.

```verilog
module Test_Bottom(C,B,D);
  input B;
  input C;
  output D;
  wire B;
  wire C;
  wire D;
  wire not_b;
  not g1(not_b, B);
  and g2(D,not_b, C);
endmodule

module Test_Top(in0,in1, out);
  input in0;
  input in1;
  output out;
  wire in0;
  wire in1;
  wire out;
  Test_Bottom t1(in0,in1,out);
endmodule
```
